x^2+4y^2-2x+16y+1=0
t_2 \in A(2)
t_2(E)
\xi^2+\eta^2=1
 x^2+4y^2-2x+16y+1=x^2-2x+1+4(y^2+4y+4)-16=(x-1)^2+4(y+2)^2-16=0 \\ \frac{(x-1)^2}{16}+\frac{(y+2)^2}4=1 
 \xi = \frac{x-1}4 \\ \eta= \frac{y+2}2 
\mathbf x' = A \mathbf x + \mathbf b
 \left [ \begin{array}{c} \xi \\ \eta \end{array}\right ] = f \left ( \left [ \begin{array}{c} x \\ y \end{array}\right ]\right ) = \left [ \begin{array}{c} \frac x4 - \frac 14 \\ \frac y2 + 1 \end{array}\right ] = \left [ \begin{array}{cc} \frac 14 & 0 \\ 0 & \frac 12 \end{array} \right ] \left [ \begin{array}{c} x \\ y \end{array}\right ] + \left [ \begin{array}{c} -\frac 14 \\ 1 \end{array}\right ] 
